      "title": {
        "rendered": "Filip&#8217;s Graduation"
      },
      "content": {
        "rendered": "<style> .filip { padding: 0 10px 0 0; } </style>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http://img.faculty.unlv.edu/lab/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/psychology-header-IMG-6.jpg\" alt=\"Header\" width=\"814\" height=\"170\"></p>\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"814\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td height=\"142\">\n<h1>Filip Bjelica</h1>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"814\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td height=\"10\">\n<p class=\"body\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"filip\" src=\"http://img.faculty.unlv.edu/lab/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Filip-author-photo-DONE.jpg\" alt=\"filip\" width=\"242\" height=\"250\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"0\" vspace=\"0\">Filip Bjelica has been a member of the Interactive Measurement Group since the fall 2019. During his time in the lab, Filip has assumed various roles and responsibilities. He has served as the lab’s website coordinator, an action editor for the newsletter, and a poster team leader. He has presented workshops and led lab members in team-building activities. He has also co-authored three research posters and presented them at various conferences.</p>\n<p class=\"body\">This spring, Filip will graduate from UNLV with a bachelor’s degree in Psychology with a minor in Criminal Justice. After graduating, Filip hopes to pursue graduate school abroad, in either the Netherlands or the United Kingdom, to study sports psychology.</p>\n<p class=\"body\">Congratulations, Filip!</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr size=\"15\">\n",
        "protected": false
      },
